Steps
Created two users: Jane and Bob
Created two security groups: Accounting and Sales
Added Jane to the Accounting group
Added Bob to the Sales group
Created two folders: Accounting and Sales
Configured NTFS permissions so:
Accounting group → full access to Accounting folder
Sales group → full access to Sales folder
No cross‑access between groups
Logged in as each user to verify access control
Confirmed least‑privilege enforcement
What I learned 
How RBAC works in Windows
How to create and manage local users and groups
How NTFS permissions map to role‑based groups
How least‑privilege prevents unauthorized access
How Windows enforces folder‑level access control
Fundamentals of identity and access management (IAM)
